&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and proactive client services professional who is ready to own our client relationships for the execution of our high-touch campaigns. The Account Manager will be responsible for maintaining and growing revenue across Tubi’s client base. The Account Manager will focus on managing the day-to-day success of our campaigns by providing best-in-class service and strategic support to our clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;This is a hybrid role based out of our New York office. You must be willing to travel to our New York office four days/week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales and clients to understand campaign objectives, and execute campaigns accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the programmatic and direct landscape to help clients accomplish their goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Pre Sales team to understand plan components and deal terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for creating and implementing timelines and touchpoints to manage the campaign process from IO approval and deal creation through day to day management and billing IO campaigns&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create direct and programmatic campaigns in Tubi’s Order Management System&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support clients &amp;amp; sales by providing best-in-class services around all aspects of campaign execution, including but not limited to screenshots, internal and external pacing reports, incremental asks, and campaign wrap reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize third party and proprietary data to analyze campaign performance and delivery&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Ad Operations to review campaign set up, monitor pace and performance, and troubleshoot technical issues or discrepancies across direct and programmatic campaigns to ensure full delivery&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Circulate final campaign performance with internal teams to provide actionable recommendations for improving future campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Background:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years relevant job experience required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in digital advertising, specifically understanding the digital video landscape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with DSPs and SSPs encouraged&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel skills and the ability to manage &amp;amp; analyze large sets of data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task in a fast-paced environment with keen attention to details&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with fantastic follow through&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of problem-solving and providing solutions to problems proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate interest in Technology, Internet, Entertainment and/or Advertising&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
