&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tubi&#39;s Creative Studio is looking for an Associate Creative Director to lead creative across a diverse and high-visibility range of work - integrated consumer campaigns for high-profile large scale sporting events, on-air and broadcast promos, event and sales sizzles, product feature videos, and B2B ad sponsorship creative. This is a senior IC role for a strategic, collaborative creative leader - someone who can sell an idea as compellingly as they can oversee the execution of it. &lt;strong&gt;You&#39;ll help shape work that earns attention, sparks conversation, and reinforces Tubi as one of the most culturally relevant entertainment brands&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll report to the Sr. Creative Director and work closely with art directors, motion designers, designers, copywriters, editors, and cross-functional partners across Marketing, Sales, Content, and Product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;This is a hybrid role based out of our Los Angeles office. You must be willing to travel to our Los Angeles&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;office three days/week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drives creative strategy, brief writing, and concepting across consumer campaigns, on-air/broadcast promos, event sizzles, product explainers, and B2B ad/sponsorship creative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversees static digital design across B2B and B2C creative - ensuring consistency, craft, and on-brand execution across all formats and placements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Presents unfinished ideas comfortably, facilitates creative discussions, and influences senior stakeholders through strong storytelling and creative rationale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shapes motion graphics and animation deliverables by providing clear creative direction and notes on pacing, visual style, and brand alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directs B2B sponsorship creative from brief through delivery, ensuring work is strategically sound and on-brand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partners with Producers and Creative Operations to manage timelines, prioritize workload, and maintain quality across a high volume of concurrent projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shows up as a genuine collaborator and team player - contributing to a creative culture built on trust, generosity, and shared ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborates with Marketing, Sales, Content, Product, and other XFN teams to ensure creative is integrated, strategic, and effective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drives AI adoption across creative workflows - identifying and implementing tools that elevate the team&#39;s speed, quality, and creative thinkingStay ahead of trends in brand, broadcast, digital advertising, social, and motion to continuously raise the creative bar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Background:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of creative experience building culturally resonant work for consumer entertainment, streaming, media, gaming, or creator platforms, or at a leading creative agency recognized for breakthrough, earned-media campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience leading creative that has been produced for broadcast or other mass-reach consumer channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional creative strategist - able to translate business objectives into compelling creative territories and present them in a way that lands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A natural presenter and storyteller who can hold a room, build enthusiasm, and communicate the &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; behind every creative decision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong concepting and strategic thinking across both B2C and B2B creative contexts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to lead and give sharp notes on design, animation, editorial, and copywriting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated abilit

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tubi is one of the largest free streaming platforms in the US, serving a large-scale streaming audience across Web, iOS, Android, Roku, Fire TV, Apple TV, and game consoles. Quality at this scale isn&#39;t a checkbox — it&#39;s a competitive advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an Automation Engineering Manager&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to lead the team responsible for building and operating Tubi&#39;s multi-platform test automation infrastructure. You will own the strategy, tooling, and execution quality across our client surfaces — from video playback and ad delivery to content discovery and onboarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for a hands-on technical leader who can set direction, influence cross-functional roadmaps, and stay close enough to the code to guide architecture, review critical implementation decisions, and unblock complex technical issues. You will build a team that ships reliable automation at speed — and you will help the team move toward AI-native automation practices: fluent in AI tooling, proactive about applying it, and disciplined about using it responsibly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid role based out of either our San Francisco or Toronto office. You must be willing to travel to either location at least 2 days a week.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Test Strategy &amp;amp; Quality Planning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and own Tubi&#39;s multi-platform automation strategy — covering Web, iOS, Android, CTV (Roku, Fire TV, Apple TV, Smart TVs, game consoles), and API layers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish testing standards, coverage targets, and quality gate policies across the CI/CD pipeline to protect release confidence and production reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design specialized test strategies for business-critical scenarios: video playback (HLS/DASH), ad insertion, content recommendation surfaces, and user authentication flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI-assisted analysis (e.g., failure pattern clustering, test gap detection) to continuously improve test strategy based on real production signal and defect trends — not gut instinct.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automation Framework &amp;amp; Infrastructure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and maintenance of scalable, cross-platform automation frameworks built for Tubi&#39;s unique device matrix and streaming use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure automation suites are reliable, fast, and integrated as quality gates in CI/CD — owning execution health, not just test coverage numbers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously build and evolve AI-augmented engineering workflows/system that fundamentally change how the team creates, maintains, and improves automation — going beyond adopting existing tools to designing new patterns, custom integrations, and repeatable practices that raise the team&#39;s output ceiling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the team&#39;s AI capability growth: identify high-leverage AI applications in the automation lifecycle (e.g., AI-assisted test case generation, intelligent flaky cases detection, regression root cause summarization), prototype them, and codify them into team standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and selectively adopt emerging testing tools and AI-for-testing innovations. Translate promising external ideas into concrete, team-specific workflows, and make sure adoption leads to measurable improvements in speed, reliability, and engineering quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership &amp;amp; Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow a team of automation engineers: set clear individual goals, run regular 1:1s, create concrete career development plans, and hold a high bar for technical execution.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tubi is looking for a Coordinator to join our Creative Studio team. This role plays a key part in supporting the successful execution of Originals marketing campaigns by owning the operational workflows, systems, and project infrastructure that keep campaigns moving from planning through delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with Producers, Creative Directors, and cross-functional partners, the Coordinator ensures projects are organized, assets are managed, documentation is maintained, and operational processes are executed consistently across all assigned projects and workflows. This role is ideal for someone who is highly organized, detail-oriented, proactive, and excited to build efficient workflows that enable creative teams to do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Coordinator partners closely with Producers throughout the campaign lifecycle, owning day-to-day operational execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;This is a hybrid role based out of our Los Angeles office. You must be willing to travel to our Los Angeles&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;office two days/week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own project setup and campaign infrastructure for assigned campaigns and workflows, including creating project records, folder structures, project documentation, and other materials needed to support campaigns from planning through delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain project briefs, review documents, deliverable trackers, and project documentation, ensuring campaigns are organized, execution-ready, and accurately tracked throughout the project lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate project data in Airtable, perform ongoing audits to ensure data integrity, and support continuous improvements to team workflows and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate creative review logistics by preparing review materials, scheduling meetings, tracking feedback and approvals, maintaining project documentation, and ensuring review materials are distributed to the appropriate stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage creative assets throughout the campaign lifecycle, including tracking incoming media, organizing assets across Frame.io, Google Drive, and other systems, validating deliveries, and coordinating final asset distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate on-set photography operations by managing on-set brief workflows, tracking production milestones, confirming asset deliveries, maintaining photography archives, and ensuring required materials are received and organized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate vendor operations, including onboarding support, tracking scope requests and approvals, and managing invoice collection, validation, and routing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Content team and production partners to monitor production schedules, casting updates, asset availability, and other key project milestones, proactively following up on missing information and deliverables, and communicating potential impacts to Producers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support delivery operations by organizing final deliverables, coordinating asset distribution to internal stakeholders, tracking required documentation, and ensuring projects are properly closed out.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare agendas, meeting notes, action items, and recurring project updates for team and cross-functional meetings while maintaining documentation and shared resources that support efficient team operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing project updates, leadership presentations, and other recurring reporting to communicate project status and team priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify opportunities to improve operational workflows, documentation, and team processes to drive greater efficiency acros

&lt;p&gt;Data Scientist (Tubi, Inc.; San Francisco, California): Work with large and complex data sets to solve a wide array of challenging problems using different analytical and statistical approaches. Apply technical expertise with quantitative analysis, experimentation, data mining, and the presentation of data to develop strategies for our products. Create and manage dashboards and visualizations, delivering actionable insights to stakeholders and enabling data-informed decision-making. Partner with Product, Engineering, and cross-functional teams to inform, influence, support, and execute strategy and investment decisions. Ensure statistical rigor, metric alignment, transparency, and effectiveness in Tubi’s decision-making processes. Design, evaluate, and refine experimentation frameworks, including pre-test planning, in-flight monitoring, and post-experiment analysis. Define, understand, and test opportunities and levers to improve the product, and drive roadmaps through your insights and recommendations. Join forces with Data Engineering to ensure the availability and integrity of data required for analytics, ML ops for deployment, and opportunities for automation. Telecommuting permitted pursuant to company policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary&lt;/strong&gt;: $174,000 – 191,400 per year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;: Master’s degree or foreign equivalent in Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, or related field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Three (3) years of experience in the position offered or related occupation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must have experience with the following:&lt;/strong&gt; analytics and SQL, Python, and Spark; A/B testing, experimental design, and causal inference in a technology-driven environment; extracting insights from large datasets using statistical methods; product analytics and working with event-level data; and video streaming industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any interested applicant may click on the APPLY NOW button above to apply for this position&lt;/p&gt;
