&lt;p&gt;Tubi is redefining what free streaming can be. Built boldly for every fandom, Tubi delivers the largest library of movies and TV shows on the planet, spanning Hollywood hits, cult classics, creator-led stories, and an ever-growing slate of Tubi Originals crafted for passionate audiences. With over 100 million monthly active users and a footprint that makes us the most-watched free streaming service in the U.S. and Canada, we’re on a mission to give everyone access to the world’s stories.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the heart of Tubi’s experience is the player: the moment a user presses play and the world around them dissolves into a story. Tubi’s Player team owns the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;core player UX and video playback experience&lt;/strong&gt; across every platform: CTV, mobile, and web. From the first frame to the final second, this team shapes how over 100 million monthly active users watch, discover, and engage our library, and drives Tubi’s most important business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Senior Product Manager for our Player Experience to lead the vision, strategy, and execution for this team. This role sits at the intersection of innovation in UI/UX design, rigorous experimentation, and technical video infrastructure, owning everything from playback controls and in-player discovery surfaces to the live TV experience, and AI-powered UX features that are redefining how users interact with content. This is a high-impact, high-visibility role for a PM who thrives on building groundbreaking UX, moving fast through data, and thinking deeply about what the future of streaming feels like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid role based out of our San Francisco office. You must be willing to travel to our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;San Francisco &lt;/strong&gt;office two days/week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the Player roadmap: &lt;/strong&gt;Define product strategy, OKRs, and success metrics targeting view time, revenue, and engagement across Tubi’s playback surfaces, from pre-roll through post-play. Translate the team’s H1 and annual bets into a coherent, prioritized plan and maintain ruthless focus on the highest-leverage investments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design innovative playback UI/UX: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead a high-velocity program to build best-in-class playback experiences, including dynamic post-play flows, browse-while-watching surfaces, in-player content discovery, and AI driven experiences that push what a player UI can do. You don’t just iterate on existing patterns; you conceive of experiences users didn’t know they wanted and have the conviction to ship them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive a world-class A/B testing program: &lt;/strong&gt;Own the end-to-end experimentation lifecycle for player experiences, from hypothesis design to instrumentation to analysis. Run dozens of concurrent experiments, maintain rigorous testing methodology, and translate complex behavioral signals from large-scale experiments into decisive, fast-moving product bets. Your experiments should consistently compound into measurable view time and revenue lift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape AI-powered features: &lt;/strong&gt;Define and ship AI-driven features across both the user-facing playback experience and backend player operations. This includes intelligent features that deepen content engagement during playback and leveraging AI to accelerate player diagnostics, experiment analysis, and operational efficiency, making the team faster without sacrificing quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the live TV viewing experience: &lt;/strong&gt;Drive strategy and execution for Tubi’s linear channel product, including the EPG (electronic program guide), channel playback, and the end-to-end viewer journey for scheduled prog

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Senior Product Manager, Search to lead strategy and execution for Tubi’s Search experience and foundational search capabilities. With a library of 300,000+ titles, this role is central to how viewers discover content with intent, whether they arrive with a specific title in mind or have a broader mood or genre in mind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own key parts of the end-to-end Search experience, spanning the core search interface and the underlying capabilities that power it, including query understanding, semantic retrieval, ranking and re-ranking, result organization, autocomplete, and conversational search foundations. You’ll work closely with engineering, machine learning, design, data science, and cross-functional partners to make search faster, smarter, and more useful for millions of viewers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re passionate about building consumer search products, partnering closely with technical teams, and using data and experimentation to improve discovery, this is the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid role based out of our San Francisco office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive the product roadmap for Search, aligning near-term execution with Tubi’s broader discovery, engagement, and retention strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the core end-to-end Search experience including query entry, results, refinement, and conversational search interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-function teams including ML, engineering, data science, and design, to improve foundational search capabilities and deliver intuitive, high-quality discovery experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance search relevance and effectiveness across a variety of user needs, from precise lookups to more exploratory discovery journeys.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead experimentation to improve search quality and user outcomes, using A/B testing, behavioral analysis, and qualitative insights to iterate quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with broader teams to ensure Search capabilities can be extended effectively across surfaces and use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the user by deeply understanding viewer intent, search pain points, and moments where Search can better guide users to the right content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive high-quality cross-functional execution, ensuring teams stay aligned on goals, tradeoffs, milestones, and measurable outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Background:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of product management experience, with meaningful experience in consumer products, search, discovery, recommendations, or other relevance-driven systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of leading complex, cross-functional initiatives from strategy through execution in fast-paced, data-driven environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of search and discovery concepts such as retrieval, ranking, relevance, query intent, autocomplete, filtering, or content organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience partnering closely with engineering, data science, and/or machine learning teams on technical products or algorithmically driven user experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and experimentation skills, including defining metrics, structuring A/B tests, and translating results into product decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to balance technical constraints, user needs, and business goals in ambiguous problem spaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to align technical and non-technical stakeholders around a clear plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for building consumer experiences that are intuitive, useful, and grounded in real user behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tubi&#39;s Core Experience Backend team is responsible for building the high-performance, secure, and scalable systems that power our business. We have built disaster-resilient systems to ensure Tubi APIs continue to perform even under extreme traffic conditions. Our team and services have delivered seamless operations for massive events such as the Super Bowl and World Cup while consistently delivering a great experience to our viewers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On this team, you will participate in major campaigns, contribute to our critical backend services, support multiple platforms, and play a key role in shaping and refining the overall backend architecture.&lt;/p&gt;
