&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Staff Software Engineer who combines deep technical expertise with strong organizational influence. This role operates beyond individual service ownership and requires demonstrated impact across teams, domains, and large-scale distributed systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;This is a hybrid role based out of either our SF or NYC office. You must be willing to travel to our SF or NYC office 3 days/week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive architectural direction across multiple services and teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and evolution of distributed systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure systems are built for long-term scalability, resilience, observability, and security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-team technical alignment across client, infrastructure, product, ads, and content organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor senior engineers and elevate engineering standards across the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own critical system design decisions that impact multiple platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to domain leadership in areas such as Linear systems, EPG platforms, or time-based content architectures (preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape and evolve Tubi’s backend development practices, including AI-native engineering workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to support business-critical needs outside regular working hours when necessary, like oncall and live events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong sense of ownership, with proactive attention to on-call situations and production stability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated cross-team leadership, with familiarity working across multiple teams in complex organizational environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Background:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience designing and operating large-scale distributed systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in backend development (Elixir and Rust preferred, or strong background in comparable languages)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong architectural judgment with proven cross-team technical leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with gRPC/Protocol Buffers, RESTful APIs, Kubernetes, and observability systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to lead complex, cross-functional initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills with the ability to articulate trade-offs and drive alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in high-traffic, mission-critical production environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Linear content systems, EPG platforms, or other time-based scheduling architectures is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience building or supporting systems for large-scale live events (e.g., major sports tournaments) with high concurrency and real-time demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus/Preferred:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep production experience in Elixir &amp;amp; Rust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep production experience with Pingora or Nginx&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Kubernetes experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior ownership of large-scale architectural transformations&lt;/li&gt;
